Introduction

Learning penetration testing requires hands-on practice with real vulnerabilities. Platforms like TryHackMe provide excellent labs to develop these skills.
In this report, I will explain my walkthrough of the Basic Pentesting room. The objective of this lab is to practice enumeration, brute-force attacks, and gaining access to a target machine.
During the lab, I used several penetration testing tools to identify vulnerabilities and obtain system access.
Lab Setup

To start the lab, I connected to the TryHackMe VPN and deployed the target machine.
Tools used in this challenge:

Nmap

Gobuster

Hydra

SSH

These tools help discover open services, hidden directories, and weak credentials.
Step 1: Network Scanning

The first step in penetration testing is identifying open ports and running services.
I used Nmap to scan the target machine.
nmap -sC -sV <target-ip>
